## Build and Launch Instructions

### Prerequisites

- Java JDK 11 or higher installed
- Apache Maven installed
- Apache Tomcat 11 installed
- NetBeans IDE (or any Maven-compatible IDE)

### Step 1 — Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Menuka-Irindu/Smart-Campus-REST-API.git
cd smartcampusapi
```

### Step 2 — Build the Project

Using Maven from the command line:

```bash
mvn clean package
```

Or in NetBeans:
- Right-click the project → **Clean and Build**
- Wait for: `BUILD SUCCESS`

### Step 3 — Start Apache Tomcat

In NetBeans:
- Go to **Window → Services** (Ctrl + 5)
- Expand **Servers**
- Right-click **Apache Tomcat** → **Start**
- Wait for the Output window to show:
  ```
  INFO: Server startup in [XXXX] milliseconds
  ```

### Step 4 — Deploy the Project

In NetBeans:
- Right-click the project → **Run**
- NetBeans will deploy the WAR file to Tomcat automatically

### Step 5 — Verify the API is Running

Open your browser or Postman and send:

```
GET http://localhost:8080/smartcampusapi/api/v1/
```

You should receive:

```json
{
    "name": "Smart Campus API",
    "version": "v1",
    "contact": "admin@smartcampus.ac.uk",
    "resources": {
        "rooms": "/api/v1/rooms",
        "sensors": "/api/v1/sensors"
    }
}
```

> **Note:** All data is stored in-memory. Data resets every time Tomcat restarts.  
> Always create Rooms before Sensors when testing.

---

## API Endpoints

### Discovery

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Status |
|--------|----------|-------------|--------|
| GET | `/api/v1/` | Returns API metadata and resource links | 200 |

### Rooms

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Success Status |
|--------|----------|-------------|----------------|
| GET | `/api/v1/rooms` | List all rooms | 200 |
| POST | `/api/v1/rooms` | Create a new room | 201 |
| GET | `/api/v1/rooms/{roomId}` | Get a room by ID | 200 |
| DELETE | `/api/v1/rooms/{roomId}` | Delete a room (blocked if sensors exist) | 204 |

### Sensors

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Success Status |
|--------|----------|-------------|----------------|
| GET | `/api/v1/sensors` | List all sensors | 200 |
| GET | `/api/v1/sensors?type=CO2` | List sensors filtered by type | 200 |
| POST | `/api/v1/sensors` | Register a new sensor | 201 |
| GET | `/api/v1/sensors/{sensorId}` | Get a sensor by ID | 200 |

### Sensor Readings (Sub-Resource)

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Success Status |
|--------|----------|-------------|----------------|
| GET | `/api/v1/sensors/{sensorId}/readings` | Get reading history | 200 |
| POST | `/api/v1/sensors/{sensorId}/readings` | Add a new reading | 201 |

### Error Responses

| Status | Scenario |
|--------|----------|
| 403 Forbidden | POST reading to a MAINTENANCE sensor |
| 404 Not Found | Resource does not exist |
| 409 Conflict | DELETE room that still has sensors |
| 422 Unprocessable Entity | POST sensor with non-existent roomId |
| 500 Internal Server Error | Any unexpected server error |

---

## Sample curl Commands

### 1. Get Discovery Endpoint

```bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/smartcampusapi/api/v1/
```

### 2. Create a Room

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/smartcampusapi/api/v1/rooms \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"id\":\"LIB-301\",\"name\":\"Library Study Room\",\"capacity\":30}"
```

### 3. Create a Sensor linked to LIB-301

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/smartcampusapi/api/v1/sensors \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"id\":\"TEMP-001\",\"type\":\"Temperature\",\"status\":\"ACTIVE\",\"currentValue\":0.0,\"roomId\":\"LIB-301\"}"
```

### 4. Get Sensors filtered by type

```bash
curl -X GET "http://localhost:8080/smartcampusapi/api/v1/sensors?type=Temperature"
```

### 5. Post a Sensor Reading

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/smartcampusapi/api/v1/sensors/TEMP-001/readings \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"value\":22.5}"
```

### 6. Get Reading History for a Sensor

```bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/smartcampusapi/api/v1/sensors/TEMP-001/readings
```

### 7. Attempt to Delete a Room with Sensors (409 Conflict)

```bash
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/smartcampusapi/api/v1/rooms/LIB-301
```

### 8. Attempt to Register Sensor with Invalid roomId (422 Unprocessable Entity)

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/smartcampusapi/api/v1/sensors \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"id\":\"FAKE-001\",\"type\":\"CO2\",\"status\":\"ACTIVE\",\"currentValue\":0.0,\"roomId\":\"FAKE-ROOM\"}"
```

### 9. Attempt to Post Reading to MAINTENANCE Sensor (403 Forbidden)

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/smartcampusapi/api/v1/sensors \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"id\":\"CO2-002\",\"type\":\"CO2\",\"status\":\"MAINTENANCE\",\"currentValue\":0.0,\"roomId\":\"LIB-301\"}"

curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/smartcampusapi/api/v1/sensors/CO2-002/readings \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"value\":500.0}"
```

### 10. Delete an Empty Room (204 No Content)

```bash
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/smartcampusapi/api/v1/rooms/HALL-101
```

